{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_6huWqKXHYvahetkJ1lo0tDa1","type":"tool_result","content":"commit 180eebd68a2fb081e70a044b53a0b076df8254ff\nAuthor:     Vasilis Kefallinos <vkefallinos@gmail.com>\nAuthorDate: Tue Jul 14 01:21:16 2026 +0300\nCommit:     Vasilis Kefallinos <vkefallinos@gmail.com>\nCommitDate: Tue Jul 14 01:21:16 2026 +0300\n\n    test(scenarios/08-small-shop): implement round-1 runner (14 Acts, 1:1 with scenario.md)\n    \n    Implements run.mjs from the template + 05-latam patterns: 6-fixture dump →\n    unprompted offer → build; research; db-emitter reorder DRAFT (never sent);\n    integrationStatus name-only; callConnection real order + SSRF/DNS-rebind guard;\n    consent DENY on disk; signed inbound + negatives; event storm; <Chat\n    agent=stock/advisor> specialist embed; Dutch update + restraint; in-app app\n    evolution; memory; restart auto-resume; app-API render layer.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\ncommit 5efc65539c04b6b5396f42040d87613768d705b6\nAuthor:     Vasilis Kefallinos <vkefallinos@gmail.com>\nAuthorDate: Tue Jul 14 14:54:39 2026 +0300\nCommit:     Vasilis Kefallinos <vkefallinos@gmail.com>\nCommitDate: Tue Jul 14 14:54:39 2026 +0300\n\n    fix(scenarios/harness): a turn whose session vanished is INTERRUPTED, not finished\n    \n    Three fixes, all from one live failure in 10-family-recipes.\n    \n    1. thing.mjs — `sawWork && !me` (the session is no longer resident) returned the\n       turn as COMPLETE. It is not: the shared local server gets restarted by whichever\n       lane just rebuilt, and a turn that had only dispatched its delegates comes back\n       with no results at all. Scenario 10 sent the user's \"yes\" into a session that had\n       never made the offer it was agreeing to, and every downstream Act failed on a\n       build that never happened. Flag it `interrupted`, exactly like the 404 path.\n    \n    2. thing.mjs — a re-established session REPLAYS its persisted trace from seq 0. We\n       already hold those events, so the replay was appended as if it were new work, and\n       `turn(startSeq)` then sliced a window of REPLAYED history and asserted on it as\n       the turn just sent. Drain the replay to re-sync lastSeq, then discard it.\n    \n    3. local.mjs — start the shared server with `--max-sessions 40`. The default (8) is\n       sized for one user's chat tabs; this server hosts every lane at once and a single\n       authoring turn adds a delegate sub-session per specialist it fans out to.\n    \n    The runner honours `interrupted` by re-sending, as a real user would.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e527c9e4-a091-4065-bd58-17ce2dd60e21","uuid":"1dc58f88-ff8d-4164-87d7-22d9cd54b977","timestamp":"2026-07-14T16:41:28.752Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"commit 180eebd68a2fb081e70a044b53a0b076df8254ff\nAuthor:     Vasilis Kefallinos <vkefallinos@gmail.com>\nAuthorDate: Tue Jul 14 01:21:16 2026 +0300\nCommit:     Vasilis Kefallinos <vkefallinos@gmail.com>\nCommitDate: Tue Jul 14 01:21:16 2026 +0300\n\n    test(scenarios/08-small-shop): implement round-1 runner (14 Acts, 1:1 with scenario.md)\n    \n    Implements run.mjs from the template + 05-latam patterns: 6-fixture dump →\n    unprompted offer → build; research; db-emitter reorder DRAFT (never sent);\n    integrationStatus name-only; callConnection real order + SSRF/DNS-rebind guard;\n    consent DENY on disk; signed inbound + negatives; event storm; <Chat\n    agent=stock/advisor> specialist embed; Dutch update + restraint; in-app app\n    evolution; memory; restart auto-resume; app-API render layer.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>\ncommit 5efc65539c04b6b5396f42040d87613768d705b6\nAuthor:     Vasilis Kefallinos <vkefallinos@gmail.com>\nAuthorDate: Tue Jul 14 14:54:39 2026 +0300\nCommit:     Vasilis Kefallinos <vkefallinos@gmail.com>\nCommitDate: Tue Jul 14 14:54:39 2026 +0300\n\n    fix(scenarios/harness): a turn whose session vanished is INTERRUPTED, not finished\n    \n    Three fixes, all from one live failure in 10-family-recipes.\n    \n    1. thing.mjs — `sawWork && !me` (the session is no longer resident) returned the\n       turn as COMPLETE. It is not: the shared local server gets restarted by whichever\n       lane just rebuilt, and a turn that had only dispatched its delegates comes back\n       with no results at all. Scenario 10 sent the user's \"yes\" into a session that had\n       never made the offer it was agreeing to, and every downstream Act failed on a\n       build that never happened. Flag it `interrupted`, exactly like the 404 path.\n    \n    2. thing.mjs — a re-established session REPLAYS its persisted trace from seq 0. We\n       already hold those events, so the replay was appended as if it were new work, and\n       `turn(startSeq)` then sliced a window of REPLAYED history and asserted on it as\n       the turn just sent. Drain the replay to re-sync lastSeq, then discard it.\n    \n    3. local.mjs — start the shared server with `--max-sessions 40`. The default (8) is\n       sized for one user's chat tabs; this server hosts every lane at once and a single\n       authoring turn adds a delegate sub-session per specialist it fans out to.\n    \n    The runner honours `interrupted` by re-sending, as a real user would.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
